nan_row_percent = Data.apply(get_percent_NaN, axis=1)

# Remove cols and rows that have lots of NaN
limit_remove_col, limit_remove_row = 80, 30 #percent
cols_should_remove = list(nan_col_percent[ nan_col_percent > limit_remove_col].index)
rows_should_remove = list(nan_row_percent[ nan_row_percent > limit_remove_row].index)
Data.drop(cols_should_remove, axis="columns", inplace=True)
Data.drop(rows_should_remove, axis="rows", inplace=True)


# fill NaN cell with mean of col
Data.fillna(Data.mean(), inplace = True)

def get_normal_col(col_data):
    return (  (col_data - col_data.mean()) / col_data.std()  )

numerical_columns = list((Data.select_dtypes(include=np.number)).columns)
numerical_columns.remove('Outcome')
standard_data = deepcopy(Data)
for col_name in numerical_columns :
    standard_data[col_name] = get_normal_col(Data[col_name])
standard_data

In [21]:
accuracy_train, accuracy_test = [], []
chosen_neighbour = [0, -1] #[ num of neighbours,  accuracy of neighbour]
best_predict = []
neighbours = range(1, 100)
for num_n in neighbours :
    classifier = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors = num_n)
    classifier.fit(train_in, train_out)
    predict_test = classifier.predict(test_in)
    new_acc_train = sm.accuracy_score(train_out, classifier.predict(train_in))
    new_acc_test = sm.accuracy_score(test_out, predict_test)
    accuracy_train.append(new_acc_train)
    accuracy_test.append(new_acc_test)
    if new_acc_test > chosen_neighbour[1] :
        chosen_neighbour[0], chosen_neighbour[1] = num_n, new_acc_test
        best_predict = predict_test
chosen_neighbour

Confusion matrix . .
$$ Accuracy = \frac{TP + TN}{TP + TN + FP + FN} $$
$$ Precision = \frac{TP}{TP + FP} $$
$$ Recall = \frac{TP}{TP + FN} $$
:

$$ Accuracy = \frac{95+38}{95+38+9+27} = \frac{133}{169} = 0.786 $$
$$ Precision = \frac{38}{38 + 9} = \frac{38}{47} = 0.808 $$
$$ Recall = \frac{38}{38 + 27} = \frac{38}{65} = 0.584 $$

In [25]:
accuracy_train, accuracy_test = [], []
chosen_depth = [0, -1] #[ depth,  accuracy of depth]
best_predict = []
depths = range(1, 40)
for depth in depths :
    classifier = tree.DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth = depth)
    classifier.fit(train_in, train_out)
    predict_test = classifier.predict(test_in)
    new_acc_train = sm.accuracy_score(train_out, classifier.predict(train_in))
    new_acc_test = sm.accuracy_score(test_out, predict_test)
    accuracy_train.append(new_acc_train)
    accuracy_test.append(new_acc_test)
    if new_acc_test > chosen_depth[1] :
        chosen_depth[0], chosen_depth[1] = depth, new_acc_test
        best_predict = predict_test
chosen_depth

accuracy_train, accuracy_test = [], []
chosen = [0, -1] 
best_predict = []
iters = range(1, 60)
for i in iters :
    classifier = RandomForestClassifier(max_depth = i)
    classifier.fit(train_in, train_out)
    predict_test = classifier.predict(test_in)
    new_acc_train = sm.accuracy_score(train_out, classifier.predict(train_in))
    new_acc_test = sm.accuracy_score(test_out, predict_test)
    accuracy_train.append(new_acc_train)
    accuracy_test.append(new_acc_test)
    if new_acc_test > chosen[1] :
        chosen[0], chosen[1] = i, new_acc_test
        best_predict = predict_test
chosen
